I reviewed the metrics, traces, and logs. Traces show frontend→adservice latency increases beginning ~19:30–19:49 (UTC+8). Metric anomalies (many JVM/GC/memory KPIs) concentrate and peak at 19:58–19:59, with the first substantial simultaneous JVM/memory KPI breaches observed at 2022-03-20 19:53:00 (UTC+8). adservice pod logs show no application error spikes, pointing to resource (JVM heap/GC) pressure rather than app errors. Based on this evidence, the most likely single root cause is service-level adservice experiencing container memory/JVM pressure leading to GC thrashing and increased latency.

